sentences: Marina Marta Vlad (born 8 March 1949) is a Romanian composer.
She studied violin with Cecilia Geanta at the Music High School in Bucharest, and graduated from the National University of Music in Bucharest in 1973.
After completing her studies, she took a position at the same school, where she taught until 2002.
